														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1284286">
									

<p>The concept is okay, DoD camouflage device that was uncontrollably succesful. But what I really like is the ingenious transport containment procedures. It changes to something other than what you think it is, so make sure everybody thinks it is dangerous and uncontainable. There's no way to know what form it will take, but it will be by definition something containable.</p>
<p>I agree with Dex. Maybe add a radius of effect limit. It can only detect information about itself within X meters, sort of thing. Alternatively, maybe tweak it so that it shifts when it detects data on its true nature rather than its current form. That way people can be aware of the obvious elephant in the room without necessarily triggering a change.</p>

							</div>

								
					
